title: UK releases military ‘space power’ doctrine
summary: The United Kingdom on Sept. 1 released “UK Space Power,” the military’s keystone doctrine publication focused on the space domain.

title: Webb telescope eyes Phantom Galaxy with mid-infrared camera
summary: Fresh images from the James Webb Space Telescope show the Phantom Galaxy in vibrant infrared light, part of a series of observations with the new $10 billion observatory to help astronomers study the formation of stars.

title: Video: Replay of Artemis 1 wet dress rehearsal, now with countdown audio
summary: More than two months after a practice countdown for the Artemis 1 launch, NASA has released audio from the launch team after gaining export control clearance. The audio provides a sneak peek of what to expect on launch day.

title: Startup OQ Technology raises $13 million to expand satellite IoT network
summary: Luxembourg startup OQ Technology said Sept. 1 that it had raised about $13 million for its planned satellite constellation to connect internet of things (IoT) devices.
